President Biden has announced the nomination of Todd Gee as U.S. Attorney and Michael Purnell and Dale Bell as U.S. Marshals in Mississippi. These nominees were chosen for their dedication to enforcing the law, professionalism, experience, commitment to equal justice, and support for the independence of the Department of Justice. Todd Gee has previously served as Deputy Chief of the Public Integrity Section of the DOJ and has experience as an Assistant U.S. Attorney in the District of Columbia. Michael Purnell has served as Lieutenant and Executive Officer of the Mississippi Highway Safety Patrol, while Dale Bell is a professional protection officer for a private security service in Hernando, Mississippi.